---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Allianz Care in Panama', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-allianz', text: 'Why Allianz for Panama', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-details', text: 'Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'retiree-considerations', text: 'Retiree Considerations', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Panama', href: '/countries/panama/insurance' },
  { title: 'Allianz Care Review', href: '/providers/allianz-care' },
  { title: 'Allianz vs Cigna', href: '/compare/allianz-care-vs-cigna-global' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price (Age 55)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Essential', coverage: 'Core inpatient', price: '$200-280/mo' },
  { plan: 'Classic', coverage: 'Inpatient + outpatient', price: '$280-380/mo' },
  { plan: 'Premium', coverage: 'Comprehensive', price: '$350-450/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Allianz Care Health Insurance in Panama"
  description="Guide to Allianz Care international health insurance for expats and retirees in Panama. Value-focused coverage with global backing."
  headline="Allianz Care in Panama"
  subheadline="Strong value proposition for Panama expats. Global insurer with competitive pricing for retirees."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/panama-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an Allianz Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Allianz Care in Panama</h2>
  <p>
    Allianz Care offers international health insurance backed by one of the world's largest insurers. For Panama expats seeking solid coverage at more competitive prices than some premium competitors, Allianz provides a strong balance of value and reliability.
  </p>
  <p>
    With flexible plan options and good coverage at Panama's private hospitals, Allianz appeals to value-conscious retirees and expats.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$250-400</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Age 55)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Global</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Coverage available</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Value</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Competitive pricing</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Allianz Panama Quote"
    description="Value-focused coverage for Panama expats."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-allianz">Why Allianz for Panama</h2>

  <h3>Competitive Pricing</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz typically costs 15-25% less than premium competitors like Cigna while offering comparable core coverage. For retirees watching their budget, this makes a meaningful difference over years of premiums.
  </p>

  <h3>Financial Strength</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz SE is one of the world's largest financial services companies. This backing provides confidence that claims will be paid and coverage maintained long-term—important for retirees who may be on the same plan for decades.
  </p>

  <h3>Panama Coverage</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Network access at Panama City's major private hospitals</li>
    <li>Direct billing arrangements available</li>
    <li>24/7 multilingual support</li>
    <li>Emergency evacuation included</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Good for Value Seekers</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      If you want comprehensive coverage without paying premium prices, Allianz offers one of the best value propositions for Panama expats. The savings add up significantly over a multi-year retirement.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 italic">
    Prices shown for healthy 55-year-old. Actual premiums vary based on age, health history, and selected options.
  </p>

  <h3>Deductible Options</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz offers various deductible levels to balance premium costs:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>$0:</strong> Full first-dollar coverage, highest premium</li>
    <li><strong>$500-1,000:</strong> Moderate savings, manageable out-of-pocket</li>
    <li><strong>$2,500-5,000:</strong> Significant premium reduction, catastrophic focus</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Area of Coverage</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Americas:</strong> Most affordable option for Panama residents</li>
    <li><strong>Worldwide excluding US:</strong> Good for those who travel but don't need US coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Worldwide:</strong> Full global coverage including US</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="coverage-details">Coverage Details</h2>

  <h3>What's Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Inpatient:</strong> Hospital stays, surgery, intensive care</li>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, specialists, lab work (Classic+)</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Worldwide emergency treatment</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Medical evacuation and repatriation</li>
    <li><strong>Cancer:</strong> Comprehensive cancer treatment coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Maternity:</strong> Available with waiting period</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Optional Add-ons</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Dental coverage</li>
    <li>Vision coverage</li>
    <li>Wellness benefits</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions: Subject to underwriting or moratorium</li>
    <li>Mental health: Limited benefits</li>
    <li>Alternative medicine: Limited or excluded</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="retiree-considerations">Retiree Considerations</h2>

  <h3>Long-term Value</h3>
  <p>
    For retirees planning to live in Panama for 15-20+ years, the lower premiums compound significantly:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>$100/month savings = $1,200/year = $18,000 over 15 years</li>
    <li>Even modest premium differences add up substantially</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Age Limits</h3>
  <p>
    Allianz accepts new applicants up to age 74 (with medical underwriting). Policies can be renewed for life once enrolled.
  </p>

  <h3>Pre-existing Conditions</h3>
  <p>
    Options for managing pre-existing conditions:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Moratorium:</strong> Conditions excluded for 2 years, then covered if stable</li>
    <li><strong>Full underwriting:</strong> Individual assessment, may cover or exclude specific conditions</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>US Coverage Consideration</h3>
  <p>
    If you need US coverage for visits home or potential medical care, factor in the additional cost. Americas-only coverage without US is significantly cheaper.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Allianz Plans"
    description="Find the right balance of coverage and cost."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/allianz-care"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Prices and coverage details are estimates. Get a personalized quote for accurate pricing based on your specific situation.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
